3.3. Gradient-based Spatial-temporal Saliency Map
In this section, we extend a previous method [31] which
generates class saliency maps for images to the video
domain. The main idea of our event recounting approach is
that, given a learned detection DevNet and a class of inter-
est, we trace back to the original input image by a backward
pass with which we can ﬁnd how each pixel affects the ﬁnal
